<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-14T23:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-14T23:36:00-05:00" n="931" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d931">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13510.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to
                                Mexico to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-14T22:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>187. Department’s No. 281, October 7, 5 p.m. Foreign Office has just
                            advised me that my note, in which I transcribed Department’s said
                            telegram, has, by order of General Carranza, “been transcribed to the
                            Convention of Generals and Governors at Aguascalientes so that said
                            Convention may decide on the same, after which Carranza will give an
                            answer.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>